rawContent:
Day-3 
14-Oct-2023 - Ranthambhore TIger Reseve

So the Final day of Ranthambhore trip. I wanted to see the Zone-3. Z3 is treated as most beautiful zone from Ranthambhore. It has nice habitat with 4 lakes. 

I opted for morning safari today and that too in canter since Gypsy were sold out. 

Being a birder the first thing that came to my mind was Brown FIsh Owl. It's reported from Z3 a lot. 

I opted for a front seat in Canter since I wanted to observer the pug marks of tiger myself. Z3 has sigting of tiger yesterday. 

We were roaming in the Zone and focussing on tiger only. On the way I found habitat quite promising for Brown FIsh Owl and requested Guide to check for it. We went inside the trail and could see Huge Banyan Tree with lot of fruit bats making noise. 

In just 1 minute we realized a Leopard is sitting in the tree. It was the moment of my trip. It graced us for like 20 minutes there and went on the back side of the tree. 

After Leopard sighting Canter safari was mostly over since it was already sunny and Guide suggested we will wrap up after this. 

Basically, Brown Fish Owl showed us a leopard. 

Hope you liked the trip report my Ranthambhore Trip. Hit me up if you need any help in planning your trip in India. 

Do share your experiences of wildlife with me. I love to hear them. 

#indiaves #TwitterNatureCommunity #wildlife

user.rawDescription: An Indian Wildlife & Bird Photographer with a life long interest in the natural world. My obsession with birds started in 2014.

quotedTweet.rawContent:
Day -2 highlights. 

Morning Safari - Zone 1 
Evening Safari - Zone 6

Mammals 
1) Sloth Bear 
2) Chinkara 
3) Spotted deer
4) Sambhar deer
5) Black tailed mongoose 

Birds

1) Barn Owl
2) Indian Scops Owls
3) Spotted Owlets
4) Black Stork
5) Wooly-Necked Stork

Trees ( learnt about identifying) 
1) Tendu - Coromandel ebony
2) Gurjan - Dipterocarpus turbinatus
3) Beheda - Terminalia bellirica
4) Gular - Ficus racemosa
5) Kadam tree - Neolamarckia cadamba

Morning Safari 

— We entered the zone 1 with great hopes of sighting Noori and Sultan tigresses with there cubs. 
— Unfortunately, forest department closed the most of the zone 1 part.
— I heard that noori’s cubs are just a week old and she has lost her kids twice and this time forest department is taking special care of them. First I was feeling sad and then felt very happy after knowing the reason of closure. 
— Though tiger was not seen in Zone 1 , but I was happy to see black stork for like 15-20 minutes. 
—I spent my time by learning about new trees. 

Evening Z6 

—Evening Safari was in z6. I love the habitat of zone 6. It definitely gives a very different landscape view of Ranthambore park. 
— There is abundance of spotted and Sambhar deer in this zone. 
— It was quite nice to see a new born baby of spotted deer. It was barely able to walk. 
— While roaming in park , my wife spotted a bear. It was so close to the jeep and eating on termites
— The Bear gave me sighting of my lifetime. It stayed around us for 20
Minutes. 
— As per guide if we haven’t stopped for bear we would have seen the Lakshmi tigress as we were heading towards it and got stopped by bear. But I don’t regret it. 
— the day ended with beautiful chinkara kid and mother followed by a barn owl.
